{
  "info": {
    "name": "ESS Client Backend API",
    "description": "Industrial-grade Postman collection for the ESS (Employee Self Service) backend.\n\nHighlights:\n- Cookie-based context: EmpID and CompanyID. The server normalizes cookies via `src/middlewares/normalizeCookies.js`.\n- Variables: `baseUrl`, `EmpID`, `CompanyID`, `reqid`, `tripid`.\n- Pre-request script auto-sets cookies in the Postman cookie jar for the active `baseUrl`.\n- Multi-tenant safety: All sensitive endpoints are scoped by `CompanyID`.\n- Environments: use the provided Local/Production template environments to switch base URL and cookie values.\n\nUsage:\n1) Import this collection and the appropriate environment (`ESS API - Local` or the Production Template).\n2) Ensure `EmpID` and `CompanyID` are set in your environment.\n3) Run requests. The collection's pre-request script will set the cookies for each request's host.\n4) For detail endpoints, set `reqid` (or `tripid`) in the environment, or use request-level params.\n\nNotes:\n- Some modules (Document, Notification, Team) contain known typos or route path issues in code (e.g., `document.routes.js` missing leading '/' for approve/reject; `notification.routes.js` uses 'broadcase' not 'broadcast'; `team.routes.js` path is 'getTeamHeirarchy'). This collection mirrors the current codebase to aid testing and discovery.\n- File upload fields: Reimbursement uses 'receipt'; Leave, BusinessTrip and Excuse use 'attachment'; Profile photo uses 'photo'.\n",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:3001", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "EmpID", "value": "E001", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "CompanyID", "value": "C001", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "reqid", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "tripid", "value": "", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Set cookies for EmpID and CompanyID before every request",
          "const base = pm.environment.get('baseUrl') || pm.collectionVariables.get('baseUrl');",
          "const emp = pm.environment.get('EmpID') || pm.collectionVariables.get('EmpID');",
          "const comp = pm.environment.get('CompanyID') || pm.collectionVariables.get('CompanyID');",
          "const jar = pm.cookies.jar();",
          "if (base && emp) { jar.set(base, 'EmpID', String(emp), function (err) { if (err) console.warn('Failed to set EmpID cookie:', err); }); }",
          "if (base && comp) { jar.set(base, 'CompanyID', String(comp), function (err) { if (err) console.warn('Failed to set CompanyID cookie:', err); }); }",
          "// Also set Context as JSON cookie so server sees req.cookies.Context.CompanyID (cookie-parser 'j:' prefix)",
          "if (base && comp) { const ctx = 'j:' + JSON.stringify({ CompanyID: String(comp) }); jar.set(base, 'Context', ctx, function (err) { if (err) console.warn('Failed to set Context cookie:', err); }); }"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "listen": "test",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Opportunistically capture request IDs from responses for chaining",
          "let data = {}; try { data = pm.response.json(); } catch (e) {}",
          "const keys = ['ReimbursementID','ReqID','requestId','requestID','tripId','LeaveReqID','LeaveID','DocumentID','ExcuseReqID','ExcuseID','BusinessTripID','FlightTicketID'];",
          "for (const k of keys) { if (data && data[k]) { pm.environment.set('reqid', String(data[k])); pm.environment.set('tripid', String(data[k])); } }"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
